Executive Profile
Donald L. Runkle  Operating Executive and Senior Executive Advisor, Tennenbaum Capital Partners, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 9 Board Members in 9 different organizations across 12 different industries.See Board Relationships71--
Background

		Mr. Donald L. Runkle, also known as Don, has been an Operating Executive of Tennenbaum Capital Partners, LLC since 2005 and serves as its Senior Executive Advisor. In this position, Mr. Runkle serves as Chairman of Eagle-Picher Corporation and serves on various other Tennenbaum portfolio company boards. Mr. Runkle served as the Chief Executive Officer at of EcoMotors International Inc. from 2009 to 2013. He served as Chief Executive Officer for four years since 2009. ... He also runs a personal consulting business. Mr. Runkle served as the Chief Technology Officer of DPH Holdings, Corp. since January 01, 2003 until 2005 and was responsible for global supply management, manufacturing and engineering oversight, research and development, aftermarket, the commercial vehicle accounts and the DaimlerChrysler account. He was also the leader for the DaimlerChrysler and Commercial Vehicle customer teams. Mr. Runkle began his career as a co-op student at Eastman Kodak and Ford Motor Company. Following graduation, he joined General Motors in 1968, where he held a variety of assignments, including Chief Engineer of Chevrolet, Chief Engineer of Powertrain and Racing at the Buick Division, Director of Advanced Vehicle Engineering, Vice President of GM's Advanced Engineering Staff and Vice President of GM's North American Engineering Center, where he was GM's top engineering executive from 1992 to 1993. He served as Special Advisor of Asia Automotive Acquisition Corp. since June 20, 2005. Mr. Runkle served as the President of Delphi Steering Division since 1993, where he led a significant turnaround and divestiture of uncompetitive assets. He served as a Vice President and President of Delphi Saginaw Division from 1993 to 1996. He served as the President of Delphi Energy & Engine Management Systems Division from 1996 to 1999. From 1998 to 1999, he co-led the IPO and spin-off of Delphi from General Motors. Mr. Runkle served as an Executive Vice President of Delphi Corporation from 2000 to 2003 with the responsibility for the Dynamics & Propulsion sector. During his tenure at Delphi, he led many international acquisitions. In 1996, he joined Delphi Corporation where he co-led the IPO process. He is a member of the Engineering Advisory Council for the University of Michigan. Mr. Runkle has been the Executive Chairman of The Board at Ioxus, Inc. since April 17, 2015. He serves as the Chairman of Autocam Corporation. He has been Member of Advisory Board of General Fusion Inc. since June 2014. He has been a Member of Strategic Advisory Board of PowerGenix Corporation since July 2008. He served as a Director of Transonic Combustion, Inc. since May 2010, VIA Motors Inc. since January 6, 2015. He has been Independent Director of  Lear Corp. since November 09, 2009. He serves as a Director on MIT's Sloan School of Management and James P. Womanck's Lean Enterprise Institute. He serves as a Member of Technical Advisory Board at Tula Technology, Inc. He serves as a Director of WinCup Corp. and Environmental Systems Products Holdings. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board of ActaCell, Inc. He was the Chairman of EaglePicher Pharmaceutical Services LLC from 2006 to 2011. He served as a Vice Chairman of DPH Holdings Corp. since January 1, 2003 until 2005 and served as its Director since 2000. As Delphi Vice-Chairman, Mr. Runkle was the senior executive for deploying lean principles, streamlining and integrating engineering, manufacturing and purchasing. He served as Executive Chairman of EcoMotors International Inc. since 2013. He serves as a Director of EcoMotors International Inc. He served as Chairman of the Board of EP Management Corporation. He served as a Director of Asia Automotive Acquisition Corp. since June 20, 2005. He was a board member of Envirotest. He has published numerous articles and papers and holds a patent for rotary engine mounting. Mr. Runkle is active in the Society of Automotive Engineers and the Society of Manufacturing Engineers. Mr. Runkle co-founded with the Department of Energy, the United States Advanced Battery Consortium (USABC). He is a life member of the Shingo Academy, which recognizes distinguished manufacturing excellence, a recipient of the Wu Manufacturing Leadership Award, which identifies role models for visionary and strategic thinking manufacturing leaders, Shingo Prize Academy Lifetime Member for distinguished manufacturing excellence and a recipient of the ASM Medal for the Advancement of Research. He is a recognized business leader and product/process innovator. Mr. Runkle earned Bachelor's and Master's degrees from the University of Michigan in Mechanical Engineering. Mr. Runkle was also a Sloan Fellow and received his Master's Degree in Business Administration/Management Science from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology.Read Full Background




